  "time_ut": 1660916677,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9\u0dca \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dad\u0dca \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dab \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Although there is a decrease in the number of Covid cases, the death rate is increasing",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The head of the World Health Organization says that the number of new corona virus infections reported globally last week has dropped by almost a quarter, but there is an increase in deaths related to Covid-19.",
        "Director General of the World Health Organization (WHO) Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus made these comments at a press conference.",
        "Tedros said there was a 35% increase in coronavirus deaths in the past month, with 15,000 deaths reported in the past week.",
        "\u201c15,000 deaths a week. This kind of death toll is completely unacceptable when we have all the tools to prevent infections and save lives.\" Tedros added."
      ],
